Film4.uk.title: Attack the Block
Film4.uk.description: (2011) Sci-fi horror-comedy with John Boyega. Aggressive aliens unwisely pick a tough London estate as the beachhead for their invasion. But the locals are no pushovers...

Film4.uk.title: Save Yourselves!
Film4.uk.description: (2020) Gentle apocalypse comedy with Sunita Mani and John Reynolds. An NYC hipster couple go cold turkey from their tech in the sticks. But while they're off grid, cute furry aliens invade.

Film4.uk.title: Lola
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Lo-fi sci-fi. In 1940, two sisters invent a contraption that intercepts future broadcasts. But it inadvertently creates an alternate timeline in which the Nazis win the war. Oops.

Film4.uk.title: The Kid Who Would Be King
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Fantasy adventure. A 12-year-old from modern-day suburbia finds King Arthur's sword Excalibur and must save the country from a sinister sorceress. With Patrick Stewart.

Film4.uk.title: Last Night in Soho Interview...
Film4.uk.description: ...Special: Director Edgar Wright and co-writer Krysty Wilson-Cairns discuss travelling through time and recreating the past to make the ingenious and atmospheric psychological thriller.

Film4.uk.title: Starman
Film4.uk.description: (1984) John Carpenter's sci-fi romance with Jeff Bridges and Karen Allen. An alien is stranded on Earth, where he assumes the form of a widow's dead husband - and finds the locals hostile.

Film4.uk.title: Miracle on 34th Street
Film4.uk.description: (1994) Festive family drama. Richard Attenborough stars as a department store Santa who insists he's the real Santa Claus. But can he prove it in court?

Film4.uk.title: Le Mans '66
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Oscar-winning sports drama starring Matt Damon and Christian Bale. In the 60s, Ford set out to build a car that can defeat Ferrari at the 24 Hours of Le Mans race.

Film4.uk.title: Boss Level
Film4.uk.description: (2020) Groundhog day shoot 'em up with Frank Grillo, Naomi Watts and Mel Gibson. Ray gets killed every day. Can he escape by unravelling the mystery of why a bunch of people want him dead?

Film4.uk.title: Gangs of New York
Film4.uk.description: (2002) Scorsese's epic drama with Leonardo DiCaprio, Daniel Day-Lewis and Cameron Diaz. As gang warfare dominates 1860s New York, an orphan seeks revenge against his father's killer.

Film4.uk.title: Straightheads
Film4.uk.description: (2007) Thriller with Gillian Anderson and Danny Dyer. On their way home from a party in the countryside, a couple are brutally attacked by thugs. Months later, they set out for vengeance.

Film4.uk.title: Daleks Invasion Earth 2150 A.D.
Film4.uk.description: (1966) A sci-fi classic with Peter Cushing. Dr Who travels to the future only to find the Daleks have conquered the Earth! Can he stop them nuking the planet's core? With Bernard Cribbins.

Film4.uk.title: Jingle All the Way
Film4.uk.description: (1996) Brian Levant's festive all-action comedy. Arnold Schwarzenegger is on a mission to get his son (Jake Lloyd) the must-have Christmas toy, Turbo Man. But it's sold out everywhere...

Film4.uk.title: Last Night in Soho Interview...
Film4.uk.description: ...Special: Director Edgar Wright and co-writer Krysty Wilson-Cairns discuss travelling through time and recreating the past to make the ingenious and atmospheric psychological thriller.

Film4.uk.title: Annie
Film4.uk.description: (2014) Jamie Foxx stars in this reboot of the 1982 musical. Orphan Annie is transported to post-2008 recession-hit New York, where she becomes the ward of a germaphobe running for mayor.

Film4.uk.title: The Day the Earth Stood Still
Film4.uk.description: (2008) Remake of the sci-fi classic with Keanu Reeves. An alien visits Earth to tell humankind to stop destroying the planet. But when he's attacked, he decides to eradicate us instead...

Film4.uk.title: Last Night in Soho Interview...
Film4.uk.description: ...Special: Director Edgar Wright and co-writer Krysty Wilson-Cairns discuss travelling through time and recreating the past to make the ingenious and atmospheric psychological thriller.

Film4.uk.description: (2020) Comedy-drama with Liam Neeson. An estranged father and son team up to fix up and sell an old Tuscan villa that their late wife and mother left to them.

Film4.uk.title: The Last Stand
Film4.uk.description: (2013) Thriller starring Arnold Schwarzenegger, Johnny Knoxville and Forest Whitaker. A small-town sheriff and his inexperienced staff take on a drug cartel boss who's fleeing to Mexico.

GBNews.uk.description: Andrew and Miriam present Monday to Thursday mornings. When the news happens, it happens here. GB News brings you the biggest stories and the answers you need from across the UK.

GBNews.uk.title: Good Afternoon Britain
GBNews.uk.description: Tackling the big stories from all angles and perspectives. Weekdays from midday, Tom Harwood and Nana Akua bring you the most compelling stories from across the United Kingdom.

GBNews.uk.title: Martin Daubney
GBNews.uk.description: Join Martin for an up-to-the-minute take on the day's events delivered in his own unique and lively style.

GBNews.uk.title: Dewbs & Co
GBNews.uk.description: Plain-speaking, straight-talking - Michelle delivers her individual take on the day's news.

GBNews.uk.title: Farage
GBNews.uk.description: Nigel Farage doesn't hold back in his GB News prime-time show. Hear his views and give your own in an hour of discussion and debate. Join Nigel as he takes on the big stories other media won't touch.

GBNews.uk.title: Jacob Rees-Mogg's State Of The Nation
GBNews.uk.description: Join Jacob for his unique and unmissable take on the day's news.

GBNews.uk.title: Patrick Christys Tonight
GBNews.uk.description: Join Patrick for two hours of spirited debate and news making interviews. Top guests tackle the issues that matter, with a sharp take on every story.

GBNews.uk.title: Patrick Christys Tonight Late Edition
GBNews.uk.description: Tomorrow's news, tonight. All the major stories making the front pages and full coverage of all the breaking news at home and abroad with Patrick Christys.
